cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with hyperspectral image classification using deep learning techniques. The use of Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) and Convolutional LSTM (ConvLSTM) also suggests that it may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the focus on modeling long-range dependencies in the spectral domain suggests that it may also belong to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the use of hyperspectral images for classification suggests that it may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
